      • findPropertyset

        public Propertyset findPropertyset(UUID id)
        Description copied from interface: PropertysetManager
        Return a propertyset identified by an UUID, or create a new propertyset with the id set if none can be found. A typical use case for creating a new propertyset with an id, is when parsing a file containing a UUID reference. In that case the propertyset is initially created and then later filled out with parsed data.
        Specified by:
        findPropertyset in interface PropertysetManager
        Parameters:
        id - identifying a Propertyset
        Returns:
        a Propertyset with a property "id" containing the id parameter

      • listAllAspects

        public Collection<Propertyset> listAllAspects()
        Description copied from interface: PropertysetManager
        Find all "aspects" that are present in memory. An aspect is a Propertyset holding property definitions (name and type of the property) of a propertyset. The aspect can be used to add more semantics to a propertyset than is actually found on on the propertyset instances. Aspects have inheritance.
        Specified by:
        listAllAspects in interface PropertysetManager
        Returns:
        a collection of Propertyset instances holding propertyset descriptions

      • findObjectsOfAspect

        public Collection<Propertyset> findObjectsOfAspect(Propertyset aspect)
        Description copied from interface: PropertysetManager
        Find all propertysets that confirm to an aspect (or, to have had an aspect applied to them. I haven't decided on the terminology here). The method will list both propertyset matching a particular aspect, and the aspects that form its supertypes.
        Specified by:
        findObjectsOfAspect in interface PropertysetManager
        Parameters:
        aspect - A Propertyset containing a propertyset definition
        Returns:
        the propertysets in memory that conform to the aspect definition
